### ============================================================================
### DrasiLib Shell Reaction Example - REST Client
### ============================================================================
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or similar tools.
###
### The HTTP source listens on port 9000 and accepts events at:
###   POST /sources/sensors/events       (single event)
###   POST /sources/sensors/events/batch (multiple events)
###
### Each event triggers the shell reaction which invokes
### `/usr/bin/python3 main.py`. Replace that command in main.rs with your own script.
### ============================================================================

### Health check - verify the HTTP source is running
GET http://localhost:9000/health

###

### ============================================================================
### INSERT OPERATIONS
### ============================================================================

### Add sensor_01 — triggers [ADD] in the shell reaction
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/sensors/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "insert",
  "element": {
    "type": "node",
    "id": "sensor_01",
    "labels": ["sensors"],
    "properties": {
      "id": "sensor_01",
      "temperature": 2.5,
      "location": "room-a"
    }
  }
}

###

### ============================================================================
### UPDATE OPERATIONS
### ============================================================================

### Update sensor_01 temperature — triggers [UPDATE] in the shell reaction
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/sensors/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "update",
  "element": {
    "type": "node",
    "id": "sensor_01",
    "labels": ["sensors"],
    "properties": {
      "id": "sensor_01",
      "temperature": 25.1,
      "location": "room-a"
    }
  }
}

###

### Add sensor_02 in a different room
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/sensors/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "insert",
  "element": {
    "type": "node",
    "id": "sensor_02",
    "labels": ["sensors"],
    "properties": {
      "id": "sensor_02",
      "temperature": 19.8,
      "location": "room-b"
    }
  }
}

###

### Update sensor_02 — temperature spike
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/sensors/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "update",
  "element": {
    "type": "node",
    "id": "sensor_02",
    "labels": ["sensors"],
    "properties": {
      "id": "sensor_02",
      "temperature": 38.5,
      "location": "room-b"
    }
  }
}

###

### ============================================================================
### DELETE OPERATIONS
### ============================================================================

### Delete sensor_01 — triggers [DELETE] in the shell reaction
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/sensors/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "delete",
  "element": {
    "type": "node",
    "id": "sensor_01",
    "labels": ["sensors"]
  }
}

###

### ============================================================================
### BATCH OPERATIONS
### ============================================================================

### Add multiple sensors at once
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/sensors/events/batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "events": [
    {
      "operation": "insert",
      "element": {
        "type": "node",
        "id": "sensor_03",
        "labels": ["sensors"],
        "properties": {
          "id": "sensor_03",
          "temperature": 21.0,
          "location": "room-c"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "operation": "insert",
      "element": {
        "type": "node",
        "id": "sensor_04",
        "labels": ["sensors"],
        "properties": {
          "id": "sensor_04",
          "temperature": 23.3,
          "location": "room-d"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
